result.execSummary:
The defendant Traza Terell Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Traza Terell Johnson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Traza Terell Johnson was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA: Francis Collins and Ryan Moertel   DF ATTY:  Alex Stormont   DF:  Traza Terell Johnson appeared. Case called at 8:30 a.m. State gives the proposed recommendations and complied with victims rights. Atty Stormont in agreement. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to Ct 5 in 14CF171. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 5 in 14CF171, disorderly conduct without the domestic abuse inhancer. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct's 1-4 in 14CF171 . Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

- Misdemeanor Court Costs of $243.00

- Impose 90 day jail sentence. Credit for 148 days jail. Time served.

**AMENDED**


It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Angela J.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

  Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

Defendant to contact Police Department to get his belongings from the property.

Maintain any current treatment program.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
